 BY SALIU SALIU CHIEF of Army Staff, Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru, has reportedly died in a plane crash, barely five months after his appointment. The air crash, it was learnt, occurred on Friday in Kaduna. The Nigerian Air Force, which confirmed the accident involving one of its aircraft in Kaduna, in a statement, did not however give details. “An air crash involving a @NigAirForce aircraft occurred this evening near the Kaduna International Airport. The immediate cause of the crash is still being ascertained. More details to follow soon,” the statement, signed by Edward Gabkwet, Director of Public Relations and Information, said. Sources however said there were eight persons on board the aircraft. Attahiru was appointed Chief of Army Staff on January 26, 2021. 